Hosts. The main hosts of the adults are large and medium-sized domestic and wild ungulates: cattle, buffaloes, camels, goats, sheep, pigs, horses and nilgai,
B. tragocamelus
. The adults have also been recorded from domestic dogs, a bear and humans (our data;
Sharif 1928
;
Kaiser & Hoogstraal 1964
;
Miranpuri & Naithani 1978
;
Geevarghese & Dhanda 1987
;
Robbins et al . 2002
).

